quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  9,48,"They sought to stir up sedition already before, and turned things upside down for thee, until the truth came, and God's command appeared, though they were averse"
  9,49,"Some of them there are that say, 'Give me leave and do not tempt me.' Have not such men fallen into temptation? And surely Gehenna encompasses the unbelievers"
  9,50,"If good fortune befalls thee, it vexes them; but if thou art visited by an affliction, they say, 'We took our dispositions before', and turn away, rejoicing"
  9,51,"Say: 'Naught shall visit us but what God has prescribed for us; He is our Protector; in God let the believers put all their trust"
  9,52,"Say: 'Are you awaiting for aught to come to us but one of the two rewards most fair? We are awaiting in your case too, for God to visit you with chastisement. from Him, or at our hands; so await; we are awaiting with you"
  9,53,"Say: 'Expend willingly, or unwillingly, it shall not be accepted from you; you are surely a people ungodly"
  9,54,"And naught prevents that their expendings should be accepted from them, but that they believe not in God and His Messenger, and perform not the prayer save lazily, and that they expend not without they are averse"